Certainly! Below is a TikZ LaTeX code snippet that generates a side-by-side bar chart comparing the Spearman Rank Correlation ($\rho$) for Linear Regression and LightGBM Regression across different numbers of training tokens and different numbers of proxy models. The y-axis labels will not include the ".00" to make the values cleaner.

```latex
\documentclass[tikz,border=5mm]{standalone}
\usepackage{pgfplots}
\pgfplotsset{compat=1.16}

\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
    \begin{axis}[
        width=7cm,
        height=8cm,
        xbar,
        symbolic y coords={2,4,6,8},
        ytick=data,
        nodes near coords,
        nodes near coords align={vertical},
        ylabel={Number of Training Tokens},
        xlabel={$\rho$ (Spearman Rank Correlation)},
        legend pos=north west,
        legend entries={Linear Regression, LightGBM Regression},
        enlarge x limits=0.2,
        ymin=-1,
        ymax=9,
        bar width=15pt
    ]
        \addplot coordinates {(0.3, 2) (0.4, 4) (0.5, 6) (0.6, 8)};
        \addlegendentry{Linear Regression}
        \addplot coordinates {(0.7, 2) (0.8, 4) (0.9, 6) (1.0, 8)};
        \addlegendentry{LightGBM Regression}
    \end{axis}
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}
```

### Explanation:
- **xbar**: Creates a horizontal bar chart.
- **symbolic y coords**: Specifies the categories for the y-axis (number of training tokens).
- **ytick=data**: Places ticks at each data point.
- **nodes near coords**: Displays the value of each bar next to it.
- **ylabel** and **xlabel**: Set the axis labels.
- **legend pos**: Positions the legend in the top-left corner.
- **enlarge x limits**: Adjusts the x-axis limits to provide some space around the bars.
- **ymin** and **ymax**: Define the range of the y-axis.
- **bar width**: Sets the width of the bars.

